						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall of the central shrine in the Chōḷēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kulaśēkharadēva: Year [.] 3, Aṟpaśi 1 = (Māṟavarman Kulaśēkhara I; c. 1268-1312 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>The king is given the title <hi rend="italic">Emmaṇḍalamum-koṇḍaruḷiya</hi> here.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is built in at the left end and the date portion cannot, therefore, be made out. It is also incomplete.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of tolls on horse, <hi rend="italic">aviḻākkaṭṭu,</hi> handloom clothes, etc., to the Śiva temple of the place to meet the expenses connected with the celebration of the annual festival of the deity, by the people of the <hi rend="italic">Patineṇ-vishayas</hi> (eighteen divisions) and the <hi rend="italic">nagarattār.</hi></p>						

						<p>Cf. Inscriptions (Texts) of the Pudukkottai State, No. 586.</p>						

						</summary>
